<subSubSection id="71A16524CE05F00AFF7CFEF5F4E2FC85" pageId="6" pageNumber="243" type="description">
<paragraph id="390436AFCE05F00AFF7CFEF5F33BFCE9" blockId="6.[151,1437,255,1111]" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="0BCFEABDCE05F00AFF7CFEF5F771FEE0" bold="true" box="[199,345,291,318]" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Description.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="FE439B4ACE05F00AFE50FEF2F4A3FEE1" box="[491,651,292,319]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.205" metricValueMax="1.24" metricValueMin="1.17" pageId="6" pageNumber="243" unit="mm" value="12.05" valueMax="12.4" valueMin="11.7">11.7–12.4 mm</quantity>
(
<quantity id="FE439B4ACE05F00AFD2CFEF2F508FEE1" box="[663,800,292,319]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.199999999999999" metricValueMax="7.3" metricValueMin="7.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="243" unit="mm" value="7.199999999999999" valueMax="7.3" valueMin="7.1">7.1–7.3 mm</quantity>
, abdomen excluded), body overall scarcely setose, almost glabrous. 
<emphasis id="0BCFEABDCE05F00AFEBDFE91F7BAFEBC" bold="true" box="[262,402,327,354]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Colouration</emphasis>
: as in diagnosis. 
<emphasis id="0BCFEABDCE05F00AFDE3FE91F4BEFEBC" bold="true" box="[600,662,327,354]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Head</emphasis>
moderately to slightly longer than wide (HW/HL= 0.8–0.9), moderately wider than pronotum at widest point (HW/ PW= 1.2); postgenal and ventral basal ridges joining each other medially; postmandibular separated from mandibular base; epicranium with medial interocular punctures separated by a distance twice as large as distance separating medial punctures from lateral punctures. Eyes distinctly shorter than temples (EL/TL = 0.6) seen from above. Antennae with first antennomere distinctly shorter than second and third combined, third about 2.0 x as long as second, fourth–eighth longer than wide, ninth–tenth about as long as wide. Labial palpus with third palpomere 1.5 x as long as second. Maxillary palpus with fourth palpomere (apical) 1.5 x as long as third. Neck about 0.4 x as wide as head at widest point. 
<emphasis id="0BCFEABDCE05F00AFCECFD92F5E4FD80" bold="true" box="[855,972,580,606]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Pronotum</emphasis>
distinctly to moderately longer than wide (PW/PL = 0.7–0.8), dorsal rows of punctures each with 5 punctures. Prosternum without distinct mid-longitudinal carina. 
<emphasis id="0BCFEABDCE05F00AFF57FD5AF70AFD78" bold="true" box="[236,290,652,678]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Legs</emphasis>
: Mesotarsi longer than mesotibiae, metatarsi shorter than metatibiae, first metarsomere shorter than fifth (S1/S5= 0.7). 
<emphasis id="0BCFEABDCE05F00AFED6FD79F79DFD14" bold="true" box="[365,437,687,714]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Elytra</emphasis>
at sides slightly to moderately longer than pronotum at midline (EtL/PL=1.1–1.2). 
<emphasis id="0BCFEABDCE05F00AFADAFD79F74BFD30" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Male sexual characters</emphasis>
: Sternum 8 slightly emarginate medio-apically, emargination without semi-membranous extension (
<figureCitation id="A1802A2ACE05F00AFF6EFD2EF731FCCC" box="[213,281,760,786]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1596,1621]" captionTargetBox="[198,1384,1137,1571]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[198,1390,1132,1571]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 8–12. Konradus leehermani, male and female genitalia [NHMUK ©]: (8) male sternum 8; (9) aedeagus in dorsal view; (10) sternum 9; (11) male tergum 10; (12) gonocoxites of female genital segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3737483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3737483/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with median lobe gradually narrowed from base into a subacute apex, internal sac with one pair of elongate and sclerotized structures (
<figureCitation id="A1802A2ACE05F00AFDC1FCCAF496FCE8" box="[634,702,796,822]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1596,1621]" captionTargetBox="[198,1384,1137,1571]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[198,1390,1132,1571]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 8–12. Konradus leehermani, male and female genitalia [NHMUK ©]: (8) male sternum 8; (9) aedeagus in dorsal view; (10) sternum 9; (11) male tergum 10; (12) gonocoxites of female genital segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3737483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3737483/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="0BCFEABDCE05F00AFD68FCCDF5D4FCE8" bold="true" box="[723,1020,795,822]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Female sexual characters</emphasis>
: As described for genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="390436AFCE05F00AFF7CFCE9F4E2FC85" blockId="6.[151,1437,255,1111]" box="[199,714,831,859]" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="0BCFEABDCE05F00AFF7CFCE9F42DFC84" bold="true" box="[199,517,831,858]" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Geographical distribution.</emphasis>
As for the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="71A16524CE05F00AFF7CFCB2F459FC7C" pageId="6" pageNumber="243" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="390436AFCE05F00AFF7CFCB2F459FC7C" blockId="6.[151,1437,255,1111]" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="0BCFEABDCE05F00AFF7CFCB2F766FCA0" bold="true" box="[199,334,868,894]" pageId="6" pageNumber="243">Etymology.</emphasis>
